What is CSS?
ways to use CSS 
property & value 
class vs id 
use of important 
display property: inline, block

Mock Interview:

Q1. What is CSS (Cascading Style Sheets), and why is it used in web development?

Q2. Describe the different ways to apply CSS styles to HTML elements.

Q3. Explain the concept of CSS properties and values. Provide examples of common CSS properties and their corresponding values.

Q4. Differentiate between using a class and an ID selector in CSS. When would you use each type of selector?

Q5. What is the !important keyword in CSS, and how does it affect style priority? Discuss best practices for using !important.

Q6. Describe the display property in CSS. Explain the differences between display: inline; and display: block;.

Q7. What are inline and block-level elements in HTML? How does the display property impact their rendering?

Q8. Explain the purpose of the float property in CSS. How can you use float to create column layouts?

Q9. Discuss the CSS position property and its values (static, relative, absolute, fixed). When would you use each position value?

Q10. How does the CSS box-sizing property affect the sizing of elements? Explain the difference between content-box and border-box.

Q11. What are CSS pseudo-classes and pseudo-elements? Provide examples of how they can be used to style elements based on states or content.

Q12. Explain the difference between margin and padding in CSS box model?

Q14. How can you use media queries in CSS for responsive web design? Provide examples of media query syntax and common use cases.
